    (function () {
        var s = document.createElement('script'); s.async = true;
        s.type = 'text/javascript';
        s.src = '//' + disqus_shortname + '.disqus.com/count.js';
        (document.getElementsByTagName('HEAD')[0] || document.getElementsByTagName('BODY')[0]).appendChild(s);
    }());
</script></aside><h2><a href="lesson-134-the-verb-lagnaa-part-1">Lesson #134: The Verb लगना lagnaa Part 1</a></h2><div class="caption clearfix rte"><p>In today&rsquo;s lesson we&rsquo;re going to begin to look at the Hindi verb <big><big>&#2354;&#2327;&#2344;&#2366; </big></big><em>lagnaa</em>. This is one of the most common verbs in Hindi and unfortunately it can also be real tricky to understand and translate sometimes, it just has so many meanings! So let&rsquo;s get straight into it, are you ready?</p><p>The most literal meaning of <big><big>&#2354;&#2327;&#2344;&#2366; </big></big><em>lagnaa </em>is &lsquo;to be attached&rsquo; or 'to be stuck&rsquo;, so we might say something like&hellip;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/e21c13a0e9333b3ac784ef5f6878f875/tumblr_inline_mhwzduxgHV1qz4rgp.png"></p><p class="center"><big><big>&#2338;&#2325;&#2381;&#2325;&#2344; &#2344;&#2361;&#2368;&#2306; &#2354;&#2327;&#2366; &#2341;&#2366;<br></big></big><em>dhakkan naheen lagaa thaa</em> <br>- The lid was not attached</p><p>That&rsquo;s easy enough yeah? Now you might be surprised to hear that in Hindi we can use this verb to talk about feelings. How does that work? Well let me show you an example to start with&hellip;</p><p><!-- more --></p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/a126480defcc3f0546b76d4bffec1c12/tumblr_inline_mhx06t0iXw1qz4rgp.png"></p><p class="center"><big><big>&#2350;&#2369;&#2333;&#2375; &#2336;&#2306;&#2337; &#2354;&#2327; &#2352;&#2361;&#2368; &#2361;&#2376;<br></big></big><em>mujhe thand lag rahee hai</em> <br>- I am (feeling) cold</p><p>What&rsquo;s happening here? Well let&rsquo;s look at the sentence literally; we&rsquo;re saying &ldquo;to me cold is attached&rdquo;. This may seem like a very odd way of saying &ldquo;I&rsquo;m cold&rdquo; in Hindi but that&rsquo;s just how we say it, that coldness is attached to you. If it helps you remember imagine a great big cold monster attaching himself to you!</p><p>Notice as well that here we&rsquo;re using the feminine form of the verb to agree with the feminine word <big><big>&#2336;&#2306;&#2337;</big></big> <em>thand</em>. A few other feelings like this follow the same pattern&hellip;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/1c37cabacce3262dfb61ad4730f92086/tumblr_inline_mhx0qb3sBt1qz4rgp.png"></p><p class="center"><big><big>&#2313;&#2360;&#2325;&#2379; &#2346;&#2381;&#2351;&#2366;&#2360; &#2354;&#2327;&#2368;</big></big> <em>usko pyaas lagee</em> <br>- He was (feeling) thirsty</p><p>Again we&rsquo;ve used exactly the same construction, we&rsquo;re literally saying &ldquo;to him thirst was attached&rdquo;. Strangle hey! One more then&hellip;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/81710941dfe6de3bdca833eb5591e2c3/tumblr_inline_mhx0zavl9W1qz4rgp.png"></p><p class="center"><big><big>&#2310;&#2342;&#2350;&#2368; &#2325;&#2379; &#2352;&#2366;&#2325;&#2381;&#2359;&#2360; &#2360;&#2375; &#2337;&#2352; &#2354;&#2327;&#2366;&nbsp;</big></big> <br><em>aadmee ko raakshas se dar lagaa</em><br>- The man was scared of the monster</p><p>Here we&rsquo;re using the word <big><big>&#2337;&#2352;</big></big> <em>dar</em> - 'fear&rsquo; to literally say &ldquo;to the man by the monster fear was attached&rdquo;, which is quite a mouthful! Can you understand and follow the sentence? Feel free to ask in comments below if you&rsquo;re at all confused!</p><p>There&rsquo;s a few other words we can use like this including <big><big>&#2349;&#2370;&#2326;</big></big> <em>bhookh</em> - hunger (fem) and <big><big>&#2327;&#2352;&#2350;&#2368;</big></big> <em>garmee</em> - heat (fem). Another word that follows the same pattern is <big><big>&#2330;&#2379;&#2335; </big></big><em>cot </em>- injury (fem). We use <big><big>&#2330;&#2379;&#2335; &#2354;&#2327;&#2344;&#2366; </big></big><em>cot lagnaa</em> to mean 'to be injured&rsquo;. The 'thing&rsquo; that gets injured or hurt is followed by a <big><big>&#2325;&#2379; </big></big><em>ko</em> and the verb is always feminine (since it always agrees with <big><big>&#2330;&#2379;&#2335; </big></big><em>cot</em>). For example&hellip;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/b60178ba38b787bacc1df56678b10091/tumblr_inline_mhx31qBJWv1qz4rgp.png"></p><p class="center"><big><big>&#2350;&#2342;&#2342;! &#2350;&#2369;&#2333;&#2375; &#2330;&#2379;&#2335; &#2354;&#2327;&#2340;&#2368; &#2361;&#2376;</big></big> <br><em>madad! mujhe cot lagtee hai</em><br>- Help! I am hurt</p><p>We can also use <big><big>&#2354;&#2327;&#2344;&#2366; </big></big><em>lagnaa</em> to mean 'seems&rsquo; in sentences where we think something is true. We might say&hellip;<em><br></em></p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/14db6222e9172885f7aa7343f921b952/tumblr_inline_mhx1y80adx1qz4rgp.png"></p><p class="center"><big><big>&#2351;&#2361; &#2360;&#2361;&#2368; &#2354;&#2327;&#2340;&#2366; &#2361;&#2376;</big></big> <br><em>yeh sahee lagtaa hai</em><br>- This seems correct</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/9e2ec872f9206d6c7475b9ff79efba94/tumblr_inline_mhx238oA511qz4rgp.png"></p><p class="center"><big><big>&#2350;&#2369;&#2333;&#2375; &#2354;&#2327;&#2340;&#2366; &#2361;&#2376; &#2325;&#2367; </big></big><big><big>&#2361;&#2367;&#2344;&#2381;&#2342;&#2368; &#2348;&#2361;&#2369;&#2340; &#2325;&#2336;&#2367;&#2344; &#2361;&#2376;</big></big> <br><em>mujhe lagtaa hai ki hindee bahut kathin hai</em><br>- To me it seems that Hindi is very difficult</p><p>Can you follow this sentence? Don&rsquo;t forget that <big><big>&#2325;&#2367; </big></big><em>ki means </em>'that&rsquo;!</p><p>Phew ok, I recon that&rsquo;s enough for today. Can you see already how versatile this verb <big><big>&#2354;&#2327;&#2344;&#2366; </big></big><em>lagnaa </em>is, it&rsquo;s already got so many meanings and uses! In Part 2 we&rsquo;ll be learning even more about this verb so be sure to <a href="../43312625462/lesson-135-the-verb-lagnaa-part-2">check it out here</a>.</p><p>To check your understanding of the lesson today try translating these sentences into Hindi. Leave your answers in the comments section below especially if you&rsquo;re not completely sure - I&rsquo;m here to help!</p><ol><li>The letter is attached</li><li>Yesterday I was so hot</li><li>Are you hungry?</li><li>Her hand was injured</li><li>To me it seems that Amit is a good man</li></ol><p>So be sure to give them a go!</p><p><a href="../43312625462/lesson-135-the-verb-lagnaa-part-2">Click here to go to Lesson #135 The Verb <big><big>&#2354;&#2327;&#2344;&#2366;</big></big> <em>lagnaa</em> Part 2</a>.</p><p><a href="../../intermediate">Back to Intermediate Grammar</a>.</p></div><aside class="post-footer"><div class="tags"><span>Tags:</span><a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/feb2013">feb2013</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE">लगना</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/lagnaa">lagnaa</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/grammar">grammar</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/verbs">verbs</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/verb">verb</a> </div><div class="bottom"><div class="like_button" data-post-id="42603252487" data-blog-name="learninghindi" id="like_button_42603252487"><iframe id="like_iframe_42603252487" src="http://assets.tumblr.com/assets/html/like_iframe.html?_v=5716f9145cbbcc5e21aa13229de5d4ed#name=learninghindi&amp;post_id=42603252487&amp;color=grey&amp;rk=N9PfZBJH" scrolling="no" width="16" height="16" frameborder="0" class="like_toggle" allowTransparency="true" name="like_iframe_42603252487"></iframe></div><a href="https://www.tumblr.com/reblog/42603252487/N9PfZBJH" class="reblog_button"style="display: block;width:16px;height:16px;"><svg width="100%" height="100%" viewBox="0 0 21 21" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.